@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
title 10 – Większy przykład: System oceniania kursów

abstract class GradePolicy {
  + {abstract} final_score(points: list[float]) : float
  + letter_grade(points: list[float]) : str
}

class MeanPolicy {
  + final_score(points: list[float]) : float
}

class BestOfTwoPolicy {
  + final_score(points: list[float]) : float
}

class WeightedPolicy {
  - _weights: list[float]
  --
  + __init__(weights: list[float])
  + final_score(points: list[float]) : float
}

class Course {
  - _name: str
  - _policy: GradePolicy
  - _students: list[Student]
  --
  + __init__(name: str, policy: GradePolicy)
  + __str__() : str
  + add_student(student: Student) : None
  + evaluate(points: list[float]) : float
  + class_report() : str
}

class Student {
  - _name: str
  - _scores: dict[str, list[float]]
  --
  + __init__(name: str)
  + __str__() : str
  + add_scores(course: str, points: list[float]) : None
  + average() : float
}

GradePolicy <|-- MeanPolicy
GradePolicy <|-- BestOfTwoPolicy
GradePolicy <|-- WeightedPolicy
Course "1" o-- "1" GradePolicy : uses
Course "1" o-- "*" Student     : contains

note top of GradePolicy
  **Strategia** (wzorzec projektowy):
  Course nie zna szczegółów obliczania –
  deleguje do GradePolicy.
  Zmiana polityki oceniania bez modyfikacji Course.
end note

note right of WeightedPolicy
  Przykład:
  weights=[0.3, 0.3, 0.4]
  scores=[60, 70, 80]
  → 60*0.3 + 70*0.3 + 80*0.4 = 74.0
end note
@enduml
